messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path:
- /api/paste/{paste_id}

Methods acceptable (based on the code as written):
- All HTTP methods acceptable: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class is annotated with @RequestMapping("/api/paste"), so every method path is relative to /api/paste.
- The delete endpoint is annotated @DeleteMapping(path = "/{paste_id}"), which yields /api/paste/{paste_id} for DELETE.
- There is also a @GetMapping(path = "/{paste_id}") method in the same controller, so GET is explicitly supported at /api/paste/{paste_id}.
- No annotations in the code declare handlers for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, PATCH, or POST on the /{paste_id} path. (There is a @PostMapping method, but it has no path and therefore maps to POST /api/paste â€” not to /api/paste/{paste_id}.)
- Per your instruction, I considered only what the code explicitly maps and did not assume framework-provided implicit handlers (e.g., automatic HEAD handling for GET).
